components.docs:
this component does nothing, but is used by the AEM zu ensure that always a webcomponent is rendered and stencil behaves as expected.
if there is no webcomponent used on a website and the webcomponents-loader is loaded, stencil does not hydrate <html> which is probably a bug.

A multi purpose input component

General behavior

- The label will be full size if there is no user input or focus on the field.

Possible configurations:

- errorMessage holds one or more error messages, hides for empty array
- button can be displayed at the end of the input field
- showInputLimits shows a counter of already used chars
- showPasswordStrength shows a password strength bar
- passwordStrength is the actual password strength

Possible input configurations:

- typeahead
If there are typeaheadOptions passed in, it will render a drop down with the given options.
The loading property will also indicate that there is process runinng.
The navigation can be done with mouse and keyboard.

- masked input
If there is a maskConfig passed in, it will used to show a input mask to support the user.

- icon input
If an icon is defined, wrap the input into a container (using the icon component)

- header input
If a container-label is defined, wrap the input into a container and set a top label
